%N A390722 Smallest integer k such that f(i,k) = 2^i*k^2 + 1 for i = 0..n are prime numbers, but not for i = n + 1.
%e A390722 a(0) = 2, because f([0],2) = [5] are all prime, while f(1,2) = 9 = 3^2 is not; no lesser number works.
%e A390722 a(2) = 1, because f([0, 1, 2],1) = [2, 3, 5] are all prime, while f(3,1) = 9 = 3^2 is not; no lesser number works.
%e A390722 a(5) = 12189840, because f([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5],12189840) = [148592199225601, 297184398451201, 594368796902401, 1188737593804801, 2377475187609601, 4754950375219201] are all prime, while f(6,12189840) = 9509900750438401 = 569 * 16713358085129 is not; no lesser number works.
%t A390722 a[n_]:=Module[{k=0},While[!AllTrue[Table[2^i*k^2+1,{i,0,n}],PrimeQ] || PrimeQ[2^(n+1)k^2+1], k++]; k]; Array[a,5,0] (* _Stefano Spezia_, Nov 16 2025 *)
